    <text>
        <group>
            <text type="letter" xml:lang="ru" xml:id="letter-00074">
                <body>
                    <opener><salute rend="inline">Петр Дмитриевич.</salute></opener>
                    <p>Апробуя поступок ваш в разсуждении запрещения, сделаннаго вами <rs
                            ref="people.xml#nov01">содержателю</rs><note type="editorial">At this
                            time Novikov was no longer the leasee of the University Typography: on 1
                            May 1789 it had been passed on to A.A. Svetushkin. By 29 September,
                            though, Svetushkin had died, and V.I. Okorokov signed a lease on the
                            Typography. Without having Eropkin's order in hand, therefore, it is
                            hard to judge to whom and to which announcement in the newspapers this
                            letter refers. (See the <ref
                                target="http://www.msu.ru/depts/MSUPubl2005/let.html">history of the
                                typography</ref> on the website of Moscow State University.)</note>
                        <rs ref="orgs.xml#mosc02">университетской типографии</rs> печатать впредь
                        непристойныя и с <name type="event" ref="events.xml#ustav01">уставом
                            благочиния</name> несогласныя объявления, соизволяем, чтоб вы таковое
                        данное от вас запрещение приказали напечатать в газетах.</p>
                    <closer><dateline><placeName ref="places.xml#pet01">В
                                С.-Петербурге.</placeName>
                            <date when-custom="1789-09-03">Сентября 3-го,
                        1789.</date></dateline></closer>
                </body>
            </text>
            <text type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <body>
                    <opener><salute rend="inline">Petr Dmitrievich.</salute></opener>
                    <p>We approve of your action regarding your prohibition leveled against the
                        leaseholder of the university typography, forbidding him to print in future
                        such indecent announcements which contravene the Police Ordinance. We assent
                        to your ordering that such a prohibition on your part be printed in the
                        newspapers.</p>
                    <closer><dateline><placeName ref="places.xml#pet01">At St
                                Petersburg.</placeName>
                            <date when-custom="1789-09-03">September 3rd,
                        1789.</date></dateline></closer>
                </body>
            </text>
